ed&quot; Rut ro. She had placed her Hate BP in the summoned bag. Lesson learned. Just say no to summoned bags. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=117524"><img src="http://home.bham.rr.com/opcode/images/Yatta1.gif"></a><br>Kubodo Borealis<br>Monk of Vis Veres<br>Click the naked Japanese guys to see my stuff</center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uizzoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Izzoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 837<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/13/02 12:17:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10840.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://media.ign.com/boards/images/icons/fatbastarddance.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tradeskill Trophies and monk bags</span><hr size=1> I personally use a LSB, Treasure Hunters Satchel, Kayruul's Mystic Pouch, and a Tink Bag. That's 40 100% WR slots, which IMO should be enough for anyone. With a little bit of looking around and some luck you can find all 4 of those for around 20k (at least on Torv)... <p><br><b>Izzoe Foshizzoe<br>Grandmaster of Torvonnilous<br><br><a href= "http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=223131" target=_blank>Inspect Me</a><br></b></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uchiangli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chiangli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(8/13/02 12:49:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=10840.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tradeskill Trophies and monk bags</span><hr size=1> Watch as I knock the conversation a bit farther askew...<br><br>Two other nice lightweight containers to consider, both of which are FREE:<br><br>    - tiny coin purse: 10-slot, 0wt, 0% WR, tiny only (given out for free in Temple of Sol Ro, great for lightweight items like gems, jewelry, HS key, etc.)<br><br>    - blood encrusted glove: 4-slot, 0.5wt, 100% WR, small only, found on ground in west wing of Howling Stones (I consider it an extra half of an LSB... almost)<br><br>I use those in addition to Naggy bag, Rallic pack, and LSB.  You'd be amazed how much fits into small and tiny slots (esp. small).  A *lot* of things you would not expect fit into a small slot.<br><br>As for the original topic, I'm a grandmaster brewer (240 + 5% geerlock).  Although it is probably the easiest to take to 250, since there are recipes that use store bought components all the way, anybody who thinks it is fast or easy to hit 250 is nuts.  It will take you a LOT of time, and you will get very very sick of making Minotaur Hero Brews.  I did it so I could make Tainted Avalanche Ales for myself and my friends, and am happy that there are now some other good recipes (e.g., Kaladim Constitutionals: +5 STA, +5 to all resists, miraculous drink).<br><br>I had planned to make a tradeskill trophy, mostly because I love clicky items and can see the value of not leaving all that FS laying around, but I haven't pulled the trigger.  The price of blue diamonds has gone through the roof, at least on Terris (typically 1500+), and I am not sure I want to burn through several (plus other expensive materials) to get the trophy, norent bags or not.  I probably will do it some day, but right now there are still better things on which to spend my coppers.<br><br>-- Kitzu, Grandmaster of the Celestial Fists<br>-- Warmaster, Scarlet Underground, Terris-Thule<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class